ius: 400 mm (15 3/4\")\r\nBridge Material: Rosewood\r\nNut Material: Urea\r\nSaddle Material: Urea\r\nBridge Pins: Black ABS with White Dot\r\nTuners: Die-Cast Chrome\r\nBody Binding: Black\r\nBody Finish: Gloss\r\nNeck Finish: Matt\r\nColor: Natural / Tobacco Brown Sunburst\r\nCase: None','Yamaha F325D Dreadnought Acoustic','','publish','open','closed','','yamaha-f325d-dreadnought-acoustic','','','2019-09-08 13:26:22','2019-09-08 13:26:22','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=product&#038;p=73',0,'product','',0),(74,1,'2019-09-08 13:21:17','2019-09-08 13:21:17','','Yamaha','','inherit','open','closed','','yamaha','','','2019-09-08 13:21:17','2019-09-08 13:21:17','',73,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Yamaha.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(75,1,'2019-09-08 13:25:46','2019-09-08 13:25:46','The Roland 60w (30w+30w) Acoustic Chorus Guitar Amplifier is a compact, portable and made specifically for acoustic guitars. It provides rich, natural stereo sound and includes built-in effects, separate guitar and mic/line channels, 48 V phantom power, magnetic and piezo pickup selectors, EQ, anti-feedback protection and a convenient mute button for silent tuning on stage. As if that wasn\'t enough, the AC-60 has a beautiful rosewood-look finish made to match acoustic guitars and compliment organic, home-like performance spaces.\r\n\r\nFor singer songwriters without a mixer or PA system the AC-60 comes equipped with two input channels - guitar and mic/line. The mic/line channel offers an XLR 1/4\" combo input to connect most any microphone or line-level instrument. Both channels provide dedicated controls for volume and multi-band EQ so they can be mixed independently for the best sound possible. Also, convenient 1/4\" and RCA AUX inputs on the rear panel allow you to connect an iPod, CD player or any other line level audio device to enhance your performances and accompany rehearsals.\r\n\r\nThroughout the years, Roland has always been known for 